Frontend

React.js — UI library
Vite — build tool / dev server
React Router DOM — page routing (/ and /admin)
Axios — API calls to backend
Tabler Icons — icon set
CSS (custom, no framework) — styling


Backend

Flask (Python) — REST API framework
Flask-CORS — handles cross-origin requests between frontend and backend
Flask-SQLAlchemy — ORM for database models
python-dotenv — manages environment variables
Gunicorn — production server (used when deployed)


Database

SQLite — local development database
PostgreSQL — production database (used when deployed on Render)


Version Control & Deployment

Git & GitHub — version control and code hosting
Vercel — frontend hosting
Render — backend + PostgreSQL hosting


Architecture pattern

REST API — Flask exposes /api/projects, /api/skills, /api/contact etc.
CRUD operations — Create, Read, Update, Delete for projects/skills via Admin Panel
Client-Server architecture — React (client) talks to Flask (server) over HTTP
